 Kingdom","Bedwelty, , Monmouth, Wales":"Bedwelty, Monmouthshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Llansawel, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Llansawel, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Gunter","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German (mainly <b>Günter</b>) and English: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Gunter</i> (Old French <i>Gontier</i>), composed of the elements <i>gund</i> ‘battle’ + <i>hari</i>, <i>heri</i> ‘army’. Compare   Guenter  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Gunterman","meanings":["Americanized form of German (North Rhine-Westphalia) <b>Guntermann</b>: elaborated form of   Gunter  . Compare   Counterman  ."]},{"name":"Gonter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Bernhardt, Frieda.  Jewish Avrohom.","German: from a variant of the personal name <i>Günter</i> (see   Gunter  ) or an altered form of   Ganter  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): occupational name, a Yiddishized form of Ukrainian <i>gontar</i> ‘shingle maker’."]},{"name":"Gonthier","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Henri, Alexandre, Andre, Chantale, Denys, Gilles, Monique, Normand, Piere, Renald.","French: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Gundhari</i>, composed of the elements <i>gund</i> ‘battle’ + <i>hari</i>, <i>heri</i> ‘army’ (see   Gunter  ). Compare   Gauthier   2.","History: Bernard Gonthier from Paris, France, married Marguerite Paquet in Quebec City, QC, in 1676."]},{"name":"Gunsch","meanings":["German (<b>Günsch</b>): from a short form of the personal name <i>Günther</i> (see   Gunter  )."]},{"name":"Gunther","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Gerhard, Fritz, Otto, Rudi, Alphons, Arno, Bernd, Dieter, Ehrhardt, Erwin, Gunther.","German (mainly <b>Günther</b>): variant of   Gunter  ."]},{"name":"Goenner","meanings":["North German (<b>Gönner</b>): from the personal name <i>Gönner</i>, a variant of   Gunter  , composed of the elements <i>gund</i> ‘battle’ + <i>hari</i>, <i>heri</i> ‘army’. Compare   Gonnerman  ."]},{"name":"Gunder","meanings":["German (also <b>Günder</b>): variant of   Gunter  ."]},{"name":"Guenter","meanings":["German (mainly <b>Günter</b>): see   Gunter  ."]}]},{"name":"Nest","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of <i>Nest</i>, a Welsh pet form of <b>Agnes</b> ; the name of the grandmother of the 12th-century chronicler Giraldus Cambrensis (‘Gerald the Welshman’)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Verch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Orlo.","German: variant of   Ferch  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferch","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."]}]},{"name":"Hir","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Widespread’; ‘broad’; also short for any name beginning with <i>Hiro</i>‐."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Nest Verch Hir Gunter was born in 1395, in Bedwelty, Monmouthshire, Wales, United Kingdom as the daughter of Richard Gunter. She married Daffydd ap Hywell in 1415, in Bedwelty, Monmouthshire, Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"1395–":"1395–Surnud","1395–Female":"1395–Surnud","1390–1450":"1390–1450","1418–1481":"1418–1481","1420–1493":"1420–1493","–Male":"Surnud","1415":"1415","1420":"1420","1395":"1395","1450":"1450","1493":"1493","1481":"1481","1418":"1418","1390":"1390","Monmouth, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Monmouth, Monmouthshire, Wales","Bedwelty, Monmouthshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Bedwelty, Monmouthshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Bedwelty, , Monmouth, Wales":"Bedw